Article I|l

Refinancing

Amounts due and not paid remaining due after the implementation of Article II hereabove on the debt of the Federal Republic of Nigeria relating to loans referred to in Article I, paragraphs 1/d) and 2/a), 1/e) and 2/a) and 1/g) and 2/a) and of which the amounts are described in Annexes X, XI and XII shall be refinanced by the Government of the

Republic of France, as soon as this agreement enters into force, as follows:

a) the Parties agree that Annexes X, XI and XII duly signed by them, shall be equivalent to a statement of the maturities which shall be refinanced up to 100% of the amounts of principal and interest described in Annexes X, XI and XII;

b) the Debt Management Office (DMO) shall give Banque de France, in the agreement to be concluded between these two institutions and referred to in Article X hereafter, a licence to debit its account for the amount of the maturities to be refinanced described in

Annexes X, XI and XII. Banque de France shall inform the DMO of these debits;

c) in order to pay the creditors, Banque de France (acting as the authorized agent of the Government of the Republic of France) shall credit on its books the DMO (acting as the authorized agent of the Government of the Federal Republic of Nigeria) with a loan equal to 100% of the maturities described in Annexes X, Xi and XII.

71

Banque de France shall simultaneously debit the DMO with the amount of this loan and credit the corresponding French creditors with the corresponding sums.

d) In case of any modification to the signed Annexes X, XI and XII, made in accordance with Article I paragraph 3/, Banque de France shall require if necessary from the DMO a complementary instruction to pay including a licence to debit its account for the refinancing of the corresponding maturities, with a breakdown for the principal and the interest. Banque de France shall inform the DMO of these debits.

On this basis, Banque de France shall then implement the provisions of paragraph c)

above for the refinancing of the corresponding amounts.

